    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft -
        Installation - Piston Cooling Tubes
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s15.4.3" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Piston Cooling Tubes</title>
        <figure id="f3450015027" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM07/M07106.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Piston cooling tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 18 bolt (8)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston cooling tube (8)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, install special patch type bolts to mount piston cooling tubes.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The bolt-on piston cooling tubes are self-aligning.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place piston cooling tubes on upper crankcase assembly mounting pad.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When installing piston cooling tube bolts, do one of the following:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install new special patch type mounting bolts (M6&#160;x&#160;18).</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove oil residue and apply
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_325.xml" xrefid="s15.t3">Liquid Gasket (RTV)</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s15.t3"/>
                    to threads of existing special patch type mounting bolts (M6&#160;x&#160;18).
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install and tighten bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_343.xml" xrefid="s19.t1">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s19.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
